  Locus:
    Chapter: 7
    Paragraph: 24
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Fit For Emperors And Kings
---
Hu Tzu said, "Just now I appeared to him as Not Yet Emerged from My
Source. I came at him empty, wriggling and turning, not knowing
anything about 'who' or 'what,' now dipping and bending, now flowing in
waves - that's why he ran away."
